1.title: Mascotas en problemas
1.plot: In Miami, the Carballo family must operate an umbilical hernia in a Shih Tzu puppy named "Titan", they also tried to save "Wags", a Labrador with a mysterious illness. Meanwhile in Hialeah, Dr. Adriana Martínez handles a case of an acute colitis with overweight symptoms in a dachshund called "Cooper". In Homestead, Dr. T urgently needs to save the life of "Cuquita" a very special pigeon that was attacked by a hawk.

2.title: Segundas oportunidades
2.plot: In Hialeah, "Mimi" a small dog with a pierced breast tumor reaches the clinic of Dr. Adriana Martinez in order to save her life, she will need two surgeries . Meanwhile in Miami, Dr. Oscar Carballo Jr. will have to deal with a complicated amputation in a cat named "Dichosa". In Homestead, Dr. T has a busy day as he first has to check up for parasites in some alpacas, then he has to review "Sugar", a mare with symptoms that could lead her to a fatal ending.

3.title: Ciclos de vida
3.plot: In Homestead, Dr. T. needs to operate urgently a dog named "Tito" who suffered serious injuries after being attacked by a pack of dogs. In downtown Miami, Dr. Oscar Carballo tries to save "Bobby", a rabbit with its hind legs paralyzed. Meanwhile in Hialeah, Dr. Adriana Martinez and his colleague Dr. Emilio Zouain, performed a complicated orthopedic surgery to a cat who has a comminuted fracture in a leg.

4.title: Emergencias y cirugías
4.plot: In the heart of Hialeah, Dr. Adriana Martinez has three emergencies happening at the same time: an extremely ill poisoned dog, a puppy with an advanced gingivitis and a pet with a dangerous corneal ulcer. In Homestead Dr. Toledo takes care of "Tori", a turtle with a serious eye infection. Meanwhile Dr. Oscar Carballo Jr. must save the life of "Gabbana", a bitch with a severe uterus infection.

imdb.title: Doctor Vet Miami
plot: Dr. Vet Miami is a reality series featuring the lives of different veterinarians, their professional and personal relationship with a wide variety of pets as well as their owners.::Carlos Salvador Gutierrez
